---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Why HealthMaps exists: free, independent, plain-language guidance for navigating Australia's mental health system."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section>
    <div class="max-w-body mx-auto px-4 pt-16 md:pt-24 pb-12 md:pb-16">
      <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-widest text-body font-semibold mb-3">The project</p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-[2.5rem] font-bold text-heading mb-5 tracking-[-0.01em] leading-tight">About HealthMaps</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-body leading-relaxed max-w-[36rem]">
        HealthMaps exists because working out where to start with mental health support shouldn't be this hard.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-paper-cream">
    <div class="max-w-body mx-auto px-4 py-16 md:py-20 space-y-14 md:space-y-16">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading mb-4">Why this site exists</h2>
        <p class="text-body leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Most people who decide to get mental health support hit the same two walls. They don't know
          what to do first — see a GP? Call a psychologist directly? What's a Mental Health Care Plan? —
          and once they're moving, they struggle to find the right practitioner without weeks of phone
          calls and guesswork.
        </p>
        <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
          HealthMaps explains the pathway step by step, in plain language: what each option costs, what
          Medicare covers, and what to actually say when you book. The kind of practical knowledge that
          people who've been through the system wish they'd had at the start.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading mb-2">What we stand for</h2>
        <dl class="border-y border-border divide-y divide-border">
          <div class="py-5 md:py-6 md:grid md:grid-cols-[11rem_1fr] md:gap-8">
            <dt class="font-semibold text-heading mb-1 md:mb-0">Free, for everyone</dt>
            <dd class="text-body leading-relaxed">
              All information on this site is free to access. There are no paywalls and no premium tiers.
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div class="py-5 md:py-6 md:grid md:grid-cols-[11rem_1fr] md:gap-8">
            <dt class="font-semibold text-heading mb-1 md:mb-0">Independent and neutral</dt>
            <dd class="text-body leading-relaxed">
              No practitioner, clinic or service pays to appear here or to be presented favourably. We
              have no commercial relationships that influence what we say.
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div class="py-5 md:py-6 md:grid md:grid-cols-[11rem_1fr] md:gap-8">
            <dt class="font-semibold text-heading mb-1 md:mb-0">Accurate and current</dt>
            <dd class="text-body leading-relaxed">
              We aim for the accuracy you'd expect from a government health service, in language you'd
              hear from a friend. Costs and Medicare details are reviewed periodically, and we say so
              when figures are estimates.
              <!-- REVIEW: confirm a review cadence you can actually commit to (e.g. "every 6 months") and state it here -->
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div class="py-5 md:py-6 md:grid md:grid-cols-[11rem_1fr] md:gap-8">
            <dt class="font-semibold text-heading mb-1 md:mb-0">Consumer-first</dt>
            <dd class="text-body leading-relaxed">
              This site is built around what people navigating the system told us they needed — not
              around what's easiest to publish.
            </dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading mb-4">Who's behind it</h2>
        <!-- REVIEW: fill in your own words — who you are, where you're based, what prompted you to build this. Only you can write this part. -->
        <p class="text-body leading-relaxed mb-4">
          HealthMaps is an independent project built by [YOUR NAME], based in [LOCATION]. It started
          from [ONE OR TWO SENTENCES — what prompted you to build this].
        </p>
        <!-- REVIEW: funding transparency — state plainly how the site is funded (self-funded? grants?). Your notes flag this as core to trust. -->
        <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
          The site is currently [self-funded / funded by …] and carries no advertising.
        </p>
      </div>

      <aside class="rounded-xl bg-bg-light border border-pencil p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-heading mb-2">What this site is not</h2>
        <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
          HealthMaps provides general information about how the Australian mental health system works.
          It isn't medical advice, it can't diagnose anything, and it's not a crisis service. If you're
          in crisis, please use the urgent help numbers available on every page of this site. For
          decisions about your own care, talk to a GP or qualified mental health professional.
          You can read more in our <a href="/disclaimer/" class="text-primary font-semibold underline underline-offset-2">full disclaimer</a>.
        </p>
      </aside>

      <div class="pt-10 border-t border-border">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-heading mb-4">Get in touch</h2>
        <p class="text-body leading-relaxed">
          Spotted something out of date? Have feedback, or a story about navigating the system that
          could help others? Email
          <!-- REVIEW: consider a dedicated address (e.g. hello@healthmaps.com.au) instead of a personal one -->
          <a href="mailto:jethrohedstrom@gmail.com" class="text-primary font-semibold underline underline-offset-2">jethrohedstrom@gmail.com</a>.
          Corrections are especially welcome — accuracy is the whole point.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
